    "Thus, together (•) g and (•) b from Corollary 5.10 form a pair of contravariant functors between these categories.We will be more specific about the type of possibility frames in the image of (•) g in the next section.",
    "(•) g and (•) b, and Dual Equivalence with Filter-Descriptive FramesLet us now consider the relation between the functor (•) g from § 5.5 and the functor (•) b from § 5.1.Proposition 5.36 (From BAOs to Frames and Back II).",
    "Given a BAO A, define η A: A → (A g) b by η A (x) = x, where x is the set of proper filters in A that contain x, as in Definition 5.29.",
    "Then:1. η A is a BAO-isomorphism; 2. if g: A → B is a BAO-homomorphism, then (g g) b • η A = η B • g, so the following diagram commutes: A (A g) b B (B g) b g η A η B (g g) bProof.",
    "For part 1, to see that η A is order-reflecting and hence injective, observe that if x ̸ ≤ A y, then x ∈ ↑x but y ̸ ∈ ↑x, so x ̸ ⊆ y."
